## Atom

For other uses, see [Atom (disambiguation)](/Atom_(disambiguation)).

**Atom**

An illustration of the [helium](/Helium) atom, depicting the [nucleus](/Atomic_nucleus) (pink) and the [electron cloud](/Electron_cloud) distribution (black). The nucleus (upper right) in helium-4 is in reality spherically symmetric and closely resembles the electron cloud, although for more complicated nuclei this is not always the case. The black bar is one [angstrom](/Angstrom) (10 −10 &#160;m or 100&#160;[pm](/Picometre)).

